Container.Overview:
Please be aware this is not my container, I only built an unRAID template for this.[br] All credit goes to coppit, if you wish to thank anyone it should be him.[br][br] This is a Docker container for running Murmur, the server for the Mumble voice-over-ip client.[br] A simple mumble-server with ini file, log, and db in your control.[br][br]
Unraid manual run Example:[br] docker run --name mumble-server -d -- restart=always --net=bridge -p 64738:64738 -p 64738:64738/udp -v /mnt/disks/DataDisk/data/murmur/:/data -t coppit/mumble-server[br]
[span style=\'color: #E80000;\']Murmur SU password [/span]will be in the log file created in your persistent directory.[br] SSH to your server and vi or nano your mumble-server.log file.[br][br] File permissions and ownership for reference:[br] mumble-server.ini {chmod 666}{chown root:root} mumble-server.log {chmod 660}{chown 108:111} mumble-server.sqlite {chmod 640}{chown 108:111}
